## 3. Pattern Discovery & Correlations

### A. Patterns in Problematic Predictions
Correlation analysis reveals the following systematic issues:

**1. Sensitivity to Object Size (Volume Bias):**
| Class | Correlation (Vol vs Dice) | Interpretation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 1 | 0.370 | Positive correlation implies model struggles with small lesions. |
| 2 | 0.414 | Positive correlation implies model struggles with small lesions. |
| 3 | 0.403 | Positive correlation implies model struggles with small lesions. |
| 4 | 0.374 | Positive correlation implies model struggles with small lesions. |

**2. Inter-Class Interference:**
* **Vol(3) vs Dice(1):** 0.447 (Large Class 3 aids Class 1.)
* **Vol(4) vs Dice(1):** -0.296 (Large Class 4 degrades Class 1 performance.)

**3. False Positive Tendencies:**
* **Class 1:** High background noise. False Positives Avg Volume is 36.5% of the average object size.
* **Class 4:** High background noise. False Positives Avg Volume is 17.3% of the average object size.

### B. Patterns in Best Cases
What defines a 'easy' case?
* **Volume Neutral:** Success does not strictly depend on total tumor burden.
